<p>Brooke groaned. "I don't know what got into me. She looked so sexy just standing there and I really wanted to dance with her and oh my god what the hell was I thinking?!" </p>
<p>Nicole watched as the blonde continued to berate herself. She had hoped that Brooke's feelings for Sam were just a passing infatuation but she knew better. If Spam was the one who made Brooke happy, then Nicole would try and be supportive. </p>
<p>That's what best friends did, right? </p>
<p>She sighed, shaking her head, not quite believing her generosity.</p>
<p><i>How many drinks have I had tonight? </i></p>
<p>"Spam wasn't exactly beating you off with a stick, Brooke." Nicole finally answered.</p>
<p>"What are you saying?" Brooke asked.</p>
<p>"I'm saying that maybe Sam feels the same way about you".</p>
<p>"So why did she leave?" Brooke countered, her heart racing at Nicole's words.</p>
<hr/>
<p>"I'm sorry Alex, I can't do this."</p>
<p>She stood up, quickly buttoning her shirt. </p>
<p>"Where are you going?" Alex asked, his voice devoid of emotion.</p>
<p>"I don't know." She replied quietly.</p>
<p>Alex stood up and walked over to Sam, gently turning her around.</p>
<p>"Stay the night. We don't have to do anything, we can just talk."</p>
<p>She shook her head. "I can't. I need to go."</p>
<p>He stepped back, frustrated. "What the hell is going on Sam?"</p>
<p>"I'm just not ready", she answered, feeling guilty. "I'm sorry."</p>
<p>He watched as Sam stood uncomfortably before him. </p>
<p>"That's not what I meant. I can wait for as long as you want me too. I love you Sam." </p>
<p>She looked away, unable to meet his gaze. </p>
<p>"I'm sorry Alex. I need to go."</p>
<p>Alex felt numb as he watched Sam go. He sank to the floor, his heart breaking.</p>
<hr/>
<p>Sam wiped away the tears as she continued walking, listening to the frantic messages Brooke had left on her phone. She contemplated going home but decided against it, not wanting to face the blonde so soon and explain why she had left the party.</p>
<p>And Alex. How many more times could she keep hurting him?</p>
<p>He told her that he loved her and she ran away like a coward. </p>
<p>It was the one thing Sam was good at. </p>
<p>Running away. </p>
<p>From Brooke. From him.</p>
<p>She didn't know what to say to his admission and Sam knew she couldn't lie. Not about that. She didn't love him the way he wanted her too. She loved Brooke, and the few minutes she had dancing in Brooke's arms were some of the happiest she ever had. </p>
<p>It nearly killed her too, realising that Brooke wouldn't love her the way Alex did.</p>
<p>So she ran to him. </p>
<p>"Love the one you're with".</p>
<p>And tried to love him.</p>
<p>Sam reached the park and walked to her favourite spot, sitting against the huge tree which overlooked the pond. She remembered as she and Alex exchanged passionate kisses, his hands moving all over her body. It wasn't until she imagined Brooke touching her that Sam began to feel anything.</p>
<p>She picked up a large rock and turned around, facing the tree. </p>
<p>There.</p>
<p>She smiled a little as she read the engraved words.</p>
<p><i>Sam loves Brooke.</i></p>
</chapter>

<chapter title="Part 18">
<p>"Brooke?"</p>
<p>"Yeah?"</p>
